sentences: Whit Dickey (born May 28, 1954) is an American free jazz drummer.
His first album as a leader was Transonic, in 1998.
Two years later, Wobbly Rail issued his Big Top.
In 2001, Dickey recorded six of his compositions with Mat Maneri, Shipp, and Rob Brown under the name Nommonsemble, resulting in the album Life Cycle.
